An articulated truck and two sedans were involved in a collision on the N4 Toll Road towards Mbombela near the Mara run-off on Wednesday March 30 at 21:00. Moeti Mmusi, the spokesperson for the Mpumalanga Department of Community Safety, Security and Liaison, said all the vehicles were travelling in the direction of Mbombela from Malalane when the crash occurred. ALSO READ: N4 spiking warning to drivers near Hectorspruit “We believe that one of the vehicles (Nissan Sentraa ) was towing the other (a Toyota Cressida) when both lost control and veered in front of a truck travelling in the same direction.” The truck smashed into the back of one of the vehicles. Three passengers were instantly killed. The truck driver escaped unharmed,” he said.  ALSO READ: Third person dies after accident between Barberton and eManzana Mmusi said investigations have already commenced. The road was partially closed to enable law enforcement and emergency personnel to work on the scene. “One of the drivers of the sedans allegedly fled the scene on foot, and the police are still looking for him,” he said.